# Document 03 — App Flow

Every page, click, and path — mapped before screens are built.

## Required sections

- Full pages list with routes and descriptions
- Navigation type (navbar, sidebar, bottom tabs)
- First screen for new visitors
- Auth flow: signup → verify → onboarding → dashboard
- 2–3 core user journeys (step-by-step)
- Empty, loading, and error states
- Modals, drawers, overlays
- Redirect logic (after login, logout, errors)

## Agent rules

- Build pages as a connected product, not isolated screens.
- Implement redirects exactly as documented.
- When adding a route, update App Flow first unless user approves an exception.
